Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara State has effected a minor cabinet reshuffle involving two ministries. The governor directed the Honourable Commissioner for Environment Abosede Olaitan Buraimoh to proceed to the Ministry of Solid Minerals. Also, the Commissioner for Planning and Economic Development Mrs. Remilekun Banigbe reverts to the Ministry of Environment. The reshuffle is with immediate effect according to a statement by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Rafiu Ajakaye in Ilorin on Monday.